abstract = {The aesthetic, organizational and technical language of operating systems architecture influences the evolutionary symbiosis of cities and technology. The system architecture must therefore relate and promulgate the DNA unique to each city. Embodying both a theoretical and applied understanding of the system and components of the smart city, the system architecture requires a meta-architecture to establish higher level guidelines. Simultaneously, city operating systems must embody diverse design principles to allow for scalability, adaptability and resilience to support each city's unique requirements and configuration as a sustainable platform. Top-down systems architecture now needs to be re-envisioned by the possibilities for systems to become themselves open, living systems, based on co-creation, co-development models as explored in the concept of the city as a living lab and open source data. With advancements in AI, city operating systems can begin to evolve as self-generating systems based on living behavioral intelligence derived from big data, real time visualization and simulation, informing the nature of system architecture as a new autopoietic language of adaptation, transformation and evolution.}
